@page "/"

<PageTitle>Callio Portal</PageTitle>

<MudStack Spacing="3">
    <MudPaper Class="callio-card callio-card-strong callio-hero" Elevation="0">
        <MudGrid>
            <MudItem xs="12" md="7">
                <div class="callio-kicker">Portal entry</div>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" GutterBottom="true">Onboard tenants, track approvals, and tune knowledge behavior in one portal.</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="callio-lead">
                    Callio Portal now covers the full early tenant journey: register the first customer user, capture the tenant request, track approval, and manage the active knowledge settings that drive the tenant's RAG experience.
                </MudText>

                <MudStack Row="true" Spacing="2" Class="mt-6">
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary" Href="/tenant-registration">Start onboarding</MudButton>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Outlined" Color="Color.Primary" Href="/tenant-request-status">Track request status</MudButton>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Href="/tenant-knowledge-settings">Knowledge settings</MudButton>
                </MudStack>
            </MudItem>

            <MudItem xs="12" md="5">
                <div class="callio-stat-row">
                    <div class="callio-stat">
                        <div class="callio-stat-label">Step 1</div>
                        <div class="callio-stat-value">Register</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="callio-stat">
                        <div class="callio-stat-label">Step 2</div>
                        <div class="callio-stat-value">Request</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="callio-stat">
                        <div class="callio-stat-label">Step 3</div>
                        <div class="callio-stat-value">Review</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </MudItem>
        </MudGrid>
    </MudPaper>

    <div class="callio-grid three">
        <MudPaper Class="callio-card pa-5" Elevation="0">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">Unified identity</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="callio-lead">
                The portal and dashboard now speak the same visual language, so customer onboarding and admin review feel like parts of one product.
            </MudText>
        </MudPaper>

        <MudPaper Class="callio-card pa-5" Elevation="0">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">Tenant-led workflow</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="callio-lead">
                The first user and tenant request are created together, which keeps onboarding focused on the tenant module instead of spreading logic across the UI.
            </MudText>
        </MudPaper>

        <MudPaper Class="callio-card pa-5" Elevation="0">
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">Knowledge controls</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="callio-lead">
                Approved tenants can now review prompts, retrieval thresholds, chunking strategy, and upload rules directly from Portal without waiting on an admin screen.
            </MudText>
        </MudPaper>
    </div>
</MudStack>
